text:
As i was scrolling down the comment section i noticed there r 2 kinds of vip. Before n after fantastic baby era. Vip (before) tends to be very supportive. Eg, "seungri is promoting his juniors" "gd+yb=mino" "mino is tabi's nephew" "psy 2.0" "gd 2.0" "seungri will be hunted down by his bb hyungs". Meanwhile SOME vips (after) tend to be more negative. Eg, "mino copying gd" "seungri should promote with my fav" "seungri copying psy". One free advice to those new vips: learn their early fights against the world...being called ugly during their debut era, tabi almost gave up his life (daesung once ran to tabi's house as soon as tabi rang him) -rumour (not 2017 incident), gd daesung's 2011 incidents, seungri scandal, bb almost disbanded. Nxt year will be my 10th year as a vip, n not supporting those they support will be the last thing i'll do. 

P/s: not all new vips are immature n not all old vips are mature. Kudos to each n every supportive vip.

text:
When BIGBANG debuted in 2006, Seungri was 15 years old (international age). 'Strong Baby' was his first solo, released in 2008, and written for him by G-Dragon. Seungri wanted to show his maturity. Funny thing, Seungri said when he was asked to sing at friends weddings, they always wanted 'Strong Baby'.

Seungri liked to DJ and was initially a dancer, so some of his music lends itself to social dancing, like the club sound at the end of 'Gotta Talk to You' or the whole dance vibe of '1,2,3'.

'Where R U From' is full of Easter eggs for fans--Panda references like the bamboo and his coat at the end of the video (because his nickname was Panda due to his dark eye circles). Once when asked what animal he would choose to be, he said a horse. It became a joke with a picture of him yawning widely compared to a horse's mouth. That's why he yawned when he dismounted the horse. So many references...

Thank you for your reaction. I always enjoy them!

text:
These kind of videos remind me of a 2012 danish film entitled, The Hunt. An innocent man is accused of a crime he did not commit by his best friend's daughter who also happened to be his student. He was arrested and when they didn't find any evidence of his acts, he was let go. The whole town turned against him and when the truth came out from that little girl's statements, no one believed her. Soon, parents of his students began saying that their children have been showing signs of molestation without stating what these signs are. He was beaten when he went to the market to buy food, his dog was killed, his son was turned into an outcast a well, and he eventually broke up with his girlfriend. He lost everything and went to his best friend to ask why he did not believe him. The man that he grew up with and treated as a brother does not believe him. He poured his disappointment, anger, frustrations, at him in the church, in front of all townspeople. Eventually, everyone started believing the little girl's truth "that it as a mistake" and reconciled with and after a year his son was included in the hunt. The film ended with a very strong and powerful message with him being almost shot in the forest when he went to see the community's hunt. A sign that he will never be welcomed.


The director of the film stated that the townspeople were not evil but good people. It's their actions that are bad. From a slip of a tongue, the world of one man, escalated to a point that people started making their own stories and lies without actual proof, and the whole community believed these liars. He was placed under the court of public opinion and torn apart when the court of law has found him not guilty. In real life, this could happen to anyone. Rumors and witch hunt theories are toxic to the community. The more it touches, the more it destroys. Like the ending of these story, later in the future, Seungri will be welcomed back into the community and they will celebrate, cry, tell stories, and make us laugh again but there are still those who will remember him as a liar, rapist, corrupt, and so forth due to these scandals. To those people, you know yourselves that you have goodness inside yourselves. Stop the toxicity of believing rumors and opinions and listen to the court of law. 


The Universal Declaration of Human Rights, article 11, states: "Everyone charged with a penal offence has the right to be presumed innocent until proved guilty according to law in a public trial at which he has had all the guarantees necessary for his defense." The negative Golden rule "Do not do unto others what you don't want others to do unto you." Heed this words that you may now your rights as a human being.

I think you asked the wrong thing. The problem is not sharing personal videos with friends, but it's filming the videos without permission of the partner and sharing it behind their backs. Most of the victims were DRUGGED and RAPED or were not aware of the hidden cameras. That's why it's such a big crime, not just because "they shouldn't share those videos cause they're public figures". 

And as a VIP who feels betrayed and was unaware of supporting a psychopath like Seungri, I'm sure that VIPs will not want him back even in the future. He let down his fans, his BB hyungs, YG ent, the whole country, and even international fans who've always praised Kpop and saluted their idols. The only good thing from this is that we get to see the truth in the Kbiz behind all those cameras thanks to him.

Edit: oh well I guess in the end many of his fans still choose to support him despite what he did. I don't blame them cause they're probably 12y/o. But if you're a female adult, please wake up and have some empathy for those women he sold and laughed about.

text: Thank you so much! I love this album. I became a VIP a few months before this was released and Riri was feeding all of us with so much content. He really wanted to fill up the space his hyungs had left by joining the military and he was desperate for their approval for this album and his first solo tour. I think he did phenomenally. He said in interviews that Alone was written thinking about his hyungs being gone and it's his favorite track.
